A '''chignon''' is a temporary swelling left on an [[infant]]'s head after a [[ventouse]] suction cap has been used to deliver him or her.<ref name="BastonDurward2010">{{cite book|last1=Baston|first1=Helen|last2=Durward|first2=Heather|title=Examination of the Newborn: A Practical Guide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0A1Cta3Q4HwC&pg=PA72|date=23 June 2010|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-84995-8|pages=72–75}}</ref> It is not a sign of serious injury and may take as little as two hours or as long as two weeks to disappear.

