{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Use British English|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Oliver Burgham |fullname = Oliver Ruck Burgham |nickname = |image = |imagesize = |caption = |birth_date = 1885 |birth_place = [[Cinderford]], [[Gloucestershire]], England<ref>Oliver R Burgham in the ''1911 Wales Census''</ref> |death_date = 1967 (aged 81)<ref>''England & Wales, Civil Registration Death Index, 1916-2007''</ref> |death_place = [[Amounderness]], [[Lancashire]], England |height = 5'11" |weight = 186 lbs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Corinthian Team Sail for Canada |url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0000687/19110729/278/0016 |work=The Yorkshire Post |date=29 July 1911 |page=16 |language=en}}</ref> |position = {{rlp|pr}}, {{rlp|HK}} |club1 = [[Ebbw Vale RLFC|Ebbw Vale]] |year1start = ≤1908 |year1end = ≥08 |appearances1 = |tries1 = |goals1 = |fieldgoals1 = |points1 = |club2 = [[Halifax R.L.F.C.|Halifax]] |year2start = ≤1911 |year2end = ≥14 |appearances2 = |tries2 = |goals2 = |fieldgoals2 = |points2 = |teamA = [[Wales national rugby league team|Wales]] |yearAstart = 1908 |yearAend = 08 |appearancesA = 2 |triesA = 1 |goalsA = 0 |fieldgoalsA = 0 |pointsA = 2 |teamB = [[Great Britain national rugby league team|Great Britain]] |yearBstart = 1911 |yearBend = |appearancesB = 1 |triesB = 0 |goalsB = 0 |fieldgoalsB = 0 |pointsB = 0 |new = yes |retired = yes |updated = 9 May 2012 |source = <ref name="Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org">{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/oliver-burgham/summary.html|title=Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org|publisher=rugbyleagueproject.org|date=31 December 2017|accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref> }}
'''Oliver Ruck Burgham''' (1885–1967) was a British professional [[rugby league]] footballer of the 1900s and 1910s. Born in [[Gloucestershire]], he played at representative level for [[Great Britain national rugby league team|Great Britain]], and [[Wales national rugby league team|Wales]], and at club level for [[Gloucester RFC|Gloucester]], [[Ebbw Vale RLFC|Ebbw Vale]], and [[Halifax R.L.F.C.|Halifax]], as a {{rlp|pr}}, or {{rlp|hk}}, i.e. number 8 or 10, or 9, during the era of [[Scrum (rugby)#Rugby league|contested scrums]].<ref name="Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org"/><ref>{{cite book|first1= Graham|last1= Williams|first2= Peter|last2= Lush|first3= David|last3= Farrar|title= The British Rugby League Records Book|publisher= London League|isbn= 978-1-903659-49-6|year= 2009|pages= 108–114}}</ref> He played at Halifax until the outbreak of the [[First World War]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Halifax Too Good for Trinity |url=https://www.britishnewspaperarchive.co.uk/viewer/bl/0000748/19140914/073/0005 |accessdate=21 June 2018 |work=Leeds Mercury |date=14 September 1914}}</ref>
==International honours== Oliver Burgham won [[Cap (sport)|cap]]s for [[Wales national rugby league team|Wales]] while at Ebbw Vale in 1908 against New Zealand, and England, and won a [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for [[Great Britain national rugby league team|Great Britain]] while at Halifax in 1911 against Australia.<ref name="Statistics at rugbyleagueproject.org"/>
