{{refimprove|date=April 2017}} '''William Bayard''' (21 August 1814 – 17 December 1907) was a distinguished [[physician]] in [[New Brunswick]]. He was the son of Dr. [[Robert Bayard]], also a noted physician and author.
Bayard was born in [[Kentville]], [[Nova Scotia]], and received his medical training in New York State and at the [[University of Edinburgh]]. He received his [[Doctor of medicine|MD]] in 1837. He then practiced medicine with his father, [[Robert Bayard]], in [[Saint John, New Brunswick]] and continued the practice after his father's death. He was the [[coroner]] of that city for 30 years.<ref name="AMB">{{Cite AMB1920|wstitle=Bayard, William}}</ref><ref name=DictCanbio>{{DictCanbio|ID=6544}}</ref>
